cmd:
> javac -version

======================================================================================================================================================================================================================
Notepad:-

FirstProgram.java:
.........................
import java.lang.*;
public class FirstProgram {
  public static void main(String[] args) {
    System.out.print("Welcome to KG Coding");
  }
}

> javac FirstProgram.java
(FirstProgram.class file is created)
> java FirstProgram

========================================================================================================================

Anatomy of a Class
......................................

Here,
public -> public so everyone can access it
class   ->   this is a class (duh)
MyFirstApp   ->   the name of this class
{    ->   opening curly brace of the class
public   ->   public so evryone can access it
static   ->   we'll cover this one later
void   ->   the return type, void means there is no value
main     ->    the name of this method
(String[] args)   ->   arguments to the method
                                 This method must be given an array of strings, and the array will be called 'args'
{   -> opening brace of the method
System.out.print   ->  this says print to standard output (defaults to command-line)
("I Rule!")    -> the string you want to print
;   -> every statement MUST end in a semicolon!!
}   ->  closing brace of the main method
}  ->  closing brace of the MyFirstApp class

===========================================================================================================
Showing Output

Example                                             Result
---------------------------------------------------------------
System.out.print("one");
System.out.print("two");                           onetwothree
System.out.println("three");
---------------------------------------------------------------
System.out.println("one");                         one
System.out.println("two");                         two   
System.out.println("three");                       three
---------------------------------------------------------------
System.out.println();                              [new line]

==============================================================================================================
FirstProgram.java :-

import java.lang.*;
public class FirstProgram {
  public static void main(String[] args) {
    System.out.print("Welcome");
    System.out.print("KG");
    System.out.print("Coding");
  }
}

> javac FirstProgram.java
> java FirstProgram

=====================
FirstProgram.java :-

import java.lang.*;
public class FirstProgram {
  public static void main(String[] args) {
    System.out.println("Welcome");
    System.out.println("KG");
    System.out.print("Coding");
  }
}

> javac FirstProgram.java
> java FirstProgram

